# Core Development Principles (Context7-aligned)

## Architecture
- Use Next.js App Router and file-based routing ([Next.js Context7](mdc:https:/context7.com/vercel/next.js)).
- Prefer Server Components for static/non-interactive UI.
- Use Client Components only for interactivity or browser APIs.
- Keep component tree shallow and composable.
- Follow unidirectional data flow patterns.
- Separate UI, logic, and data layers.

## Component Design
- Use functional React components and hooks ([React Context7](mdc:https:/context7.com/reactjs/react.dev)).
- Prefer composition and slot-based APIs (shadcn/ui).
- Extract reusable logic to custom hooks.
- Use atomic/component-driven design.

## Performance
- Use code splitting and dynamic imports.
- Memoize components and hooks.
- Use virtualization for long lists.
- Monitor and improve Core Web Vitals.

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML and ARIA attributes.
- Ensure color contrast and keyboard navigation.
- Follow accessibility guidance in shadcn/ui and TailwindCSS docs.

## Error Handling
- Use error boundaries for robust error handling.
- Handle async errors gracefully.
- Provide meaningful error messages and fallback UI.

## Security
- Sanitize user inputs.
- Use HTTPS for all communications.
- Store secrets in environment variables.
- Implement proper authentication and authorization.

## Internationalization
- Use i18n libraries/frameworks.
- Support RTL languages when necessary.
- Use translation keys, not hardcoded strings.

## Optimization
- Use lazy loading for non-critical resources.
- Use TanStack Query for server state ([TanStack Context7](mdc:https:/context7.com/tanstack/tanstack.com)).
- Optimize bundle size and critical rendering path.

